        <section id="intro" name="introduction">
            <p>
               Interaction between software and user sometimes requires more comfort, clarity, simplicity, forcing to proceed step by step.
               In these cases, wizards are the best solutions.
               
               Nowaday, the standard Java API does not provide mecanism to create wizards.
               
               the aim of <b>Awl</b>, <u>Another Wizard Library</u>, is to provide a framework which allow to easily create wizards in any Java applications
               that used a graphical user interface based on Java Swing.
               <br/><br/>
	       This site propose a <a href="tutorial.html">short tutorial</a> and <a href="documentation.html">documentation</a> on how to use Awl.
            </p>
            <p>Awl, under <a href="license.html">license LPGL 2.1</a>, is available for differents versions of Java runtime environments, 1.5 and 1.4.
            </p>
            
